The Ondo State chapter of the All Progressives Congress on Tuesday expressed sadness over the death of the wife of a former deputy governor of the state, Alhaji Ali Olanusi, Bejide. She was aged 77. Olanusi , a chieftain of the APC, was deputy to former Governor Olusegun Mimiko  between 2009 and 201. It was gathered that the deceased died on Tuesday in Akure, the state capital, during a brief illness. The state chapter of the APC has commiserated with the Olanusi’s family over the incident. This was contained in a statement by the party’s state Publicity Secretary, Mr Alex Kalejaiye. According to the statement, the deceased died on Tuesday in Akure, having complained of stress on Monday and was taken to a hospital. The statement read, “The state chairman of the party, Ade Adetimehin, described the sad development as ill-timed, shocking and unfortunate. He said Alhaja was a strong pillar behind the husband’s political success story. “The party chairman urged Baba Olanusi, the bereaved families, and entire Supare community in Akoko South West Local Government to take solace in the fact that the departed lived a worthy and fulfilled life.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com